events.description: Release of Canadian employment figures showing a fall in the unemployment rate to 6.5%.
Diplomatic discussions between the US and Iran affecting oil price volatility.
The S&P TSX Composite closed with a 1.5% gain on Friday.

facts.fact_text: The S&P TSX Composite climbed 1.5% to close above 32,471 on Friday.

evidences.evidence_text: The S&P TSX Composite climbed 1.5% to close above 32,471 on Friday

facts.fact_text: The Canadian unemployment rate fell to 6.5% in January.

evidences.evidence_text: January labour data showing the unemployment rate unexpectedly falling to 6.5%

facts.fact_text: Open Text shares surged 9.7% following strong earnings.

evidences.evidence_text: Open Text surging 9.7% after strong earnings

facts.fact_text: Gold prices surged, leading to gains in resource stocks between 2.7% and 3.7%.

evidences.evidence_text: Agnico Eagle, Barrick, Wheaton Precious Metals, and Franco Nevada gaining between 2.7% and 3.7% as gold prices surged

claims.claim_text: The unexpected fall in the unemployment rate eased near-term growth concerns.

evidences.evidence_text: unemployment rate unexpectedly falling to 6.5%, which eased near term growth concerns

claims.claim_text: A modest drop in net employment reduced expectations for a hawkish Bank of Canada stance.

evidences.evidence_text: a modest drop in net employment tempered expectations of a sharply more hawkish Bank of Canada

claims.claim_text: Strength in mining and technology stocks was sufficient to overcome general macroeconomic caution.

evidences.evidence_text: strength in mining and technology stocks outweighed lingering macro caution

evidence.evidence_text: January labour data showing the unemployment rate unexpectedly falling to 6.5%, which eased near term growth concerns
a modest drop in net employment tempered expectations of a sharply more hawkish Bank of Canada
Resource stocks also outperformed... as gold prices surged
oil prices remained volatile ahead of US Iran talks in Oman
